body.title: Grilled Chicken and Vegetable Skewers
body.description: These grilled chicken and vegetable skewers are a healthy and delicious meal option that are high in protein and fiber, low in sodium, quick to make, affordable, and healthy. The chicken is marinated in a flavorful mixture of olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, and herbs, while the vegetables are seasoned with a blend of spices. The skewers are then grilled to perfection, resulting in a tasty and satisfying meal.
ingredients: 1 lb boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into 1-inch pieces
1 red bell pepper, cut into 1-inch pieces
1 yellow bell pepper, cut into 1-inch pieces
instructions: In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, thyme, salt, and black pepper.
Add chicken to the bowl and toss to coat.
Thread chicken, bell peppers, zucchini, and red onion onto skewers.
Grill skewers for 8-10 minutes, turning occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and vegetables are tender.
